Scottish Conservative leader Douglas Ross asked Nicola Sturgeon why the Chief Executive of Scottish National Investment Bank resigned "abruptly". He said: "The chief executive of Scotland's national investment bank resigns just days before the SNP launched their own economic strategy that we've we've been underwhelming and watered down by the greens." Ms Sturgeon said she would not go into confidential details of the resignation but insisted the bank was doing vital work. THIS LIVE BLOG IS NOW CLOSED - READ COVERAGE BELOW...